# JIRA Workflow
When implementing JIRA tickets:
- Create feature branches from `develop` (or your base branch)
- Use commit message format: "TICKET-KEY: Description"
- Create PRs against `develop`
- Update JIRA with PR link when done

# Code Conventions
- Components go in src/components/
- Use existing patterns when possible
- Run linting before committing

# Testing
Before creating a PR:
- Run `npm run lint`
- Run `npm run test` (if applicable)
- Verify the feature works locally
